Zolotaya Korona (Russian: Золотая Корона, literally - Golden Crown) is a Russian payment system that provides a range of consumer payment services, including Online Card-2-Cash RUB-USD/EUR exchange service, Cash-2-Cash, Online Card-2-Cash, Online Card-2-Card money transfers, loan repayments as well as b2b payment services for banks and organizations. Zolotaya Korona is officially recognized as socially important payment system in Russia and Kazakhstan.
Participants of payment services are 550 banks, geography of operations includes 32 countries. Zolotaya Korona was created in 1994 by CFT Group. Total turnover in 2016 was 745 billion rubles.
